29 plates issued to firefighters shall bear a red Maltese cross
30 emblem on each side to the left and right of the regular tag
31 numbers. The words "Fire Fighter" should be centered at the
32 bottom of the license plate.
33 (b) In addition to any other fees provided for by law,
34 an annual additional fee of one dollar ($1.00) ten dollars
35 ($10) is added to the cost of the firefighter distinctive
36 license plate provided for in this division, effective January
37 1, 2022. The annual additional fee collected pursuant to this
38 section shall be distributed by each licensing official to the
39 state Comptroller, less the commission provided in Section
40 40-12-269. The state Comptroller shall distribute the net
41 proceeds monthly as follows:
42 (1) Fifty cents ($.50)Twenty-five percent shall be
43 deposited into a fund managed by the Alabama Joint Fire
44 Council and shall be used for the purpose of expanding and
45 maintaining the Alabama Firefighter Memorial located in
46 Tuscaloosa.
47 (2) Fifty cents ($.50)Twenty-five percent shall be
48 distributed to the Alabama Joint Fire Council to be used for
49 expenses associated with the Firefighter Peer Support Program.
50 (3) Twenty-five percent shall be distributed to the
51 board of the Alabama Firefighters Annuity and Benefit Fund.
52 (4) Twenty-five percent shall be distributed to the
53 secretary-treasurer of the Alabama Firefighters Emergency
54 Relief Fund.
