61 (a) As used in this section division, the following
62 terms shall have the following meanings:
63 (1) Professional firefighterPROFESSIONAL FIREFIGHTER.
64 means aA paid member of a paid or part-paid fire department of
65 a city, town, county, or other subdivision of the state,
66 including the chief, assistant chief, warden, engineer,
67 captain, firemen firefighters, and all other officers and
68 employees of the department who actually engage in fire
69 fighting firefighting or rendering first aid at the scene of
70 an accident.
71 (2) Retired professional firefighterRETIRED
72 PROFESSIONAL FIREFIGHTER. means aA retired member of a paid or
73 part-paid fire department of a city, town, county, or other
74 subdivision of the state, including the chief, assistant
75 chief, warden, engineer, captain, firemen firefighters, and
76 all other officers and employees of the department who
77 actually engaged in fire fighting firefighting or rendering
78 first aid at the scene of an accident. Notwithstanding any
79 other provision of this division, retired professional
80 firefighter the term includes a retired professional
81 firefighter who is a resident of this state and who has
